name: Chicken Cordon Bleu Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced shallot'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half-and-half cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh parsley, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Italian breadcrumbs, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped deli ham (about 3 ounces)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Swiss cheese, cut into 12 cubes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half-and-half cream or milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'whole grain Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}
steps: Combine shallot, half and half, parsley, egg, and 1/3 cup Italian breadcrumbs in a mixing bowl and stir together.. Add ham and chicken; season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika. Mix all ingredients together just until uniform.. Add remaining Italian bread crumbs and panko to a shallow dish and stir to combine. Roll meat mixture into 12 balls and stuff a Swiss cheese cube into the center. Roll each ball in breadcrumbs until evenly coated; place on a plate or baking sheet. Freeze meatballs for 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) and set a wire rack inside a rimmed baking sheet.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and cook until browned on all sides, 5 to 10 minutes. Transfer meatballs to the prepared wire rack.. Bake meatballs in the preheated oven until an instant read thermometer, inserted near the center, reads 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, make sauce. Wipe skillet clean and melt butter over medium heat. Whisk in flour and cook 1 minute. Whisk in broth and half-and-half. Stir in mustard, salt, and pepper and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat and simmer until sauce is rich and creamy, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.. Serve meatballs with Dijon cream sauce.

name: Slow Cooker Tuscan Chicken Meatballs with Gnocchi
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'finely chopped dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon I', 'name': 'talian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon freshly', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '2 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'reduced sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon I', 'name': 'talian seasoning'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': '1 (16-ounce) package shelf-stable', 'name': 'potato gnocchi'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5 ounce) package', 'name': 'baby spinach'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. For meatballs, preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with parchment paper.. Combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, 2 tablespoons dried tomatoes, milk, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning, salt and pepper in a bowl.. Add chicken, mix well. Shape mixture into 20 1 1/2-inch meatballs. Place in the prepared baking pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until set and lightly browned (they don’t have to be done at this point), about 15 minutes.. Add meatballs to a 3 1/2- to 4-quart slow cooker. Add broth, cream, wine, 1/3 cup dried tomatoes, and 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Cover and cook on Low 6 hours or on High 3 hours.. If using Low, turn to High. Add gnocchi. Cover and cook 20 minutes.. Stir in spinach and Parmesan cheese.. Serve hot and enjoy!

name: Chicken Piccata Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'shallots'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half and half'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'seasoned bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons finely minced', 'name': 'parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'capers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, cut into cubes'}
steps: Add half of shallots to a large bowl. Stir in Parmesan cheese, half and half, 1/3 cup bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon parsley, and egg. Roughly chop 1 tablespoon capers and add to the bowl; add ground chicken. Season with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Mix gently together until everything is well incorporated.. Add remaining bread crumbs to a work surface or shallow dish.  Form chicken mixture into 12 meatballs, rolling each one lightly in bread crumbs to coat and to help shape the meatballs.. Heat oil in a large deep skillet over medium-high heat. Add meatballs to skillet and cook, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes, adding more oil if necessary. Remove meatballs from skillet and set aside.. Add remaining shallot and capers to the skillet and cook stirring constantly, for 1 minute.  Pour in wine and stock and bring to a boil. Return meatballs to the skillet, reduce heat, and simmer until liquid is reduced by half, stirring occasionally, to coat meatballs in the sauce, 6 to 7 minutes.. Once sauce is reduced, move meatballs to one side of the skillet and turn the heat to very low. Whisk in lemon juice and cold butter, stirring constantly, until well incorporated and slightly thickened. Stir in parsley and remove from heat. Toss meatballs well with sauce and serve immediately.

name: Chicken Ricotta Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '15', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, peeled'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'basil leaves, cut into thin strips, for garnish'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'shaved Parmesan, for garnish'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with foil or parchment paper.. Heat olive oil in a skillet. Add onion and garlic, season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and cook until soft and translucent, 3 to 5 minutes. Let cool to room temperature.. Combine panko and ricotta in a bowl and mix well. Add egg and season with remaining salt, pepper and Italian seasoning; mix to combine. Add ground chicken, and cooked onion and garlic mixture; mix gently to combine.. Shape into about 24 meatballs and place on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake meatballs in the preheated oven until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C),  about 20 minutes; remove to cool.. To make the sauce, preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Coat the tomatoes with olive oil, then place cut side down in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet. Add onion and garlic cloves to the baking sheet and sprinkle everything with salt.. Roast in the preheated oven until tomato skins begin to shrivel and tomatoes begin to release their juice, about 25 minutes.. Remove and let cool slightly. Carefully discard the skins.. Place tomatoes, onion, and garlic in a blender and blend to your preferred consistency. Stir in Italian seasoning and serve with chicken meatballs. Garnish with basil and shaved Parmesan.

name: Chicken Koftas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped sweet onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves and tender stems'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mint leaves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeño chile'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry breadcrumbs or cornmeal'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Add onion, cilantro, mint, garlic, ginger, and jalapeño to a food processor; pulse until very finely chopped, about 10 (1-second) pulses. Transfer mixture to a kitchen towel, and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.. Add squeezed onion mixture, ground chicken, breadcrumbs, oil, egg, garlic powder, salt, cumin, coriander, and black pepper to a large bowl; mix gently until thoroughly incorporated.. With moistened gloved hands, shape chicken mixture into 12 (3x1-1/2-inch) cylinders and place on a baking sheet. (If grilling, shape mixture onto skewers).. To Broil: Preheat the oven’s broiler and set a rack about 7 inches from the heat source. Line a large rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil, and coat with cooking spray. Arrange koftas in a single layer about 2 inches apart, and spray with cooking spray. Broil, flipping koftas halfway through cook time, until browned and a thermometer inserted into center reads 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 8 minutes.. To Grill: Preheat grill to medium, 350 to 400 degrees F (175 to 200 degrees C). Place skewers on oiled grates; grill, covered, flipping every 2 minutes, until charred and a thermometer inserted into center reads 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 8 minutes. Alternative Method: Heat a large oiled grill pan over medium-high, about 2 minutes. Add koftas to pan; grill, uncovered, flipping every 2 minutes, until charred and a thermometer inserted into center reads 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 10 minutes.. To Air-fry: Preheat an air fryer to 380 degrees F (193 degrees C) for 2 minutes. Spray koftas with cooking spray. Working in batches if needed, add koftas to air fryer basket in a single layer, and cook, flipping after 4 minutes, until browned and a thermometer inserted into center reads  165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 8 minutes.

name: Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'orcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'granulated garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) with a rack in the top third position. Line a large-rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper, and lightly grease with 1 tablespoon of the oil.. Stir together breadcrumbs and milk in a bowl until fully combined. Let stand at room temperature until milk is fully absorbed into breadcrumbs, about 10 minutes. Add Parmesan, Italian seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, salt, onion powder, granulated garlic, and pepper to the breadcrumb mixture, and stir to combine.. Mix together chicken, egg, and 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large bowl until combined. Fold breadcrumb mixture into chicken mixture untiljust combined. Place chicken mixture in refrigerator, uncovered, andchill until firm, about 10 minutes.. Gently shape chicken mixture into 20 (1 1/2-inch balls), and place on the prepared baking sheet leaving a 1-inch space between each meatball. Brush tops and sides of meatballs with remaining 1 tablespoon oil.. Bake in the preheated oven until browned and an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of a meatball registers 165 degrees F (73 degrees C), 15 to 20 minutes, flipping after 8 minutes.

name: Harissa Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'harissa paste'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh mint (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Combine ground chicken, breadcrumbs, egg, harissa, garlic powder, salt, cumin, paprika, and black pepper in a large bowl. Mix gently with a fork or damp hands just until thoroughly combined. Shape the mixture into approximately 24 meatballs; place on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until cooked through and lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with mint. Serve hot with your favorite side dish or dipping sauce.

name: Garlic Ginger Chicken Meatball Bowls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'piece', 'name': 'fresh ginger, peeled and minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, finely minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'light soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sake'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'light soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dark soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame seed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetables'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'jasmine rice'}
steps: Combine ground chicken, garlic, ginger, onion, 1 tablespoon light soy sauce, sake, egg, panko, and green onions in a bowl. Gently mix and form into 1-inch meatballs. Place shaped meatballs onto a parchment lined tray.. For sauce, whisk together 2 teaspoons light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, honey, oyster sauce, water, and cornstarch in a bowl; set aside.. Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Using a spider or slotted spoon, carefully lower chicken meatballs into boiling water - you may have to do this in batches. Cook until meatballs float to the top, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove meatballs with a spider or slotted spoon.. Heat sesame oil in a wok. Add chicken meatballs, and cook until lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Pour sauce ingredients into the wok. Add the mixed vegetables, toss to mix. Cook until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.. Place 1/2 cup cooked jasmine rice in each bowl or on each plate. Add cooked vegetables and chicken meatballs. Serve immediately.

name: Chicken Parmesan Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 ¾', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'Italian-style panko bread crumbs, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) jar', 'name': 'marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'snipped fresh parsley (Optional)'}
steps: Stir egg, grated Parmesan cheese, 3/4 cup panko crumbs, garlic powder, Italian herb seasoning blend, crushed red pepper, salt, and black pepper together in a large bowl.. Put on a pair of food-grade disposable gloves, add chicken to the bowl, and mix with your hands until all the ingredients are well combined.. Place remaining 1 cup panko crumbs on a plate. Using a 1-1/2-inch scoop, create about 24 meatballs. Gently roll each meatball in crumbs until lightly coated; set aside on a plate.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Place 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large, oven-proof skillet over medium heat. Add half the meatballs and brown each side, turning until all sides are browned. Set this batch on a plate, and wipe the skillet clean.. Repeat with reserved oil and butter, and cook the remaining meatballs in the same way.. Wipe out the skillet again, and pour in marinara sauce. Place browned meatballs in sauce. They will not be submerged.. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle on shredded mozzarella and return to the oven for an additional 5 minutes, or until the cheese is melted. Sprinkle with fresh parsley.

Cook chicken patties in the hot oil until golden brown and no longer pink in the center, 5 to 7 minutes per side.

name: Authentic Vietnamese Spring Rolls (Nem Ran Hay Cha Gio)
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'dried thin rice noodles'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shrimp - washed, peeled, and cut into small pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrot, grated'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'wood fungus mushrooms, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': '', 'name': 'rice paper wrappers'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Soak rice noodles in cold water until soft, about 20 minutes. Drain well; cut into 2-inch long pieces.. Combine noodle pieces, chicken, shrimp, eggs, carrot, wood fungus mushrooms, and green onions in a large bowl. Add sugar, salt, and black pepper; stir well.. Soak 1 rice paper wrapper in a shallow bowl of warm water to soften, about 15 seconds. Place on a damp cloth laid out on a flat surface.. Place 1 tablespoon filling mixture into the center of softened rice paper. Fold the bottom edge into the center, covering filling. Fold in opposing edges and roll up tightly. Repeat with remaining rice paper wrappers, soaking and filling each one individually.. Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium heat.. Working in batches of 3 or 4, fry spring rolls in hot oil until crisp and golden brown on both sides, about 5 minutes. Drain on paper towels.

name: Quinoa Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'quinoa'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, or to taste, minced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': '(10 ounce) cans', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with green chile peppers (such as RO*TEL®)'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Bring chicken broth and quinoa to a boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until quinoa is tender and water has been absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Sauté onion and garlic in hot oil until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes. Add ground chicken; cook and stir until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes.. Stir cooked quinoa and diced tomatoes into chicken mixture; bring to a simmer and cook long enough for flavors to meld, about 10 minutes more.

name: Keto Chicken Crust Pizza
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese, shredded'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'freshly grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Mix ground chicken, mozzarella, Parmesan, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper together in a large bowl with your hands until well combined.. Fold in basil.. Place chicken mixture between two pieces of parchment paper.. Gently press on the top piece of parchment and spread mixture into a circle or rectangle with a thickness of 1/4 to 1/2 inch. Remove and discard the top piece of parchment paper.. Bake in the preheated oven until starting to brown on the edges, 35 to 45 minutes.

name: Homemade Grain-Free Dog Food
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'carrots, peeled and chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'apples - peeled, cored, and chopped (make sure seeds are removed)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'chicken livers, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sunflower seed oil'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'baby spinach leaves'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Place carrots, apples, and water into a pot. Bring to a boil, then cover, reduce the heat to low, and simmer until soft, 10 to 15 minutes.. Meanwhile, crack eggs into a bowl and set aside. Place eggshells onto a baking sheet.. Bake eggshells in the preheated oven until dry, 5 to 7 minutes.. Remove eggshells from the oven and pulverize using a mortar and pestle or a coffee grinder.. Combine ground chicken, chicken livers, reserved eggs, ground eggshells, and sunflower oil in a large skillet. Heat over medium heat, mixing occasionally, until chicken is browned and crumbly and livers are no longer pink, 5 to 7 minutes.. Place spinach on top of meat mixture, then cover with a lid and steam until soft, about 5 minutes.. Mash softened carrots and apples in a bowl with a potato masher and add to meat mixture. Mix until well combined.

name: Chicken Wonton Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'red cabbage, sliced and chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'carrots, peeled and grated'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coleslaw dressing'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'teriyaki sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'stir-fry sauce'}, {'quantity': '14', 'unit': '', 'name': 'wonton wrappers'}
steps: Mix together cabbage, carrots, coleslaw dressing, vinegar, soy sauce, and teriyaki in a large bowl until well combined. Place in the refrigerator until flavors blend, 1 hour to overnight.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Heat sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir ground chicken in hot oil until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Pour in stir-fry sauce. Cover the skillet, reduce heat to low, and simmer.. While chicken mixture simmers, form wonton wrappers into taco shapes and arrange between the cups of an inverted muffin tin.. Bake in the preheated oven until firm and lightly browned, 4 to 5 minutes. Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons chicken mixture into each wonton taco shell and top with slaw.. Enjoy!

name: Slow Cooker Ground Chicken Chili
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(29 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10 ounce) cans', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with green chile peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and finely chopped (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.25 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole kernel corn, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sour cream, or to taste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese, or to taste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped green onions, or to taste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, sliced, or to taste (Optional)'}
steps: Heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat in a medium-sized pan. Cook and stir ground chicken in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard grease.. Combine chili powder, garlic, cumin, and red pepper flakes in a small bowl; stir into chicken to coat.. Transfer chicken to a slow cooker. Add kidney beans, diced tomatoes with chiles, black beans, onion, and chopped jalapeno. Pour chicken broth over mixture and stir to combine.. Cover and cook on High until chili has cooked down and thickened, about 4 hours, or on Low for about 8 hours. Stir corn kernels into mixture during last 30 minutes of cook time.. Spoon chili into bowls and top each with sour cream, Cheddar cheese, green onions, and sliced jalapeno.

name: Ground Chicken Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'coarse sea salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground paprika'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate.. Place bread crumbs, onion, garlic, Parmesan cheese, salt, paprika, black pepper, and cayenne pepper into the bowl of a food processor; pulse until blended.. Combine chicken, egg, and bread crumb mixture in a large bowl until evenly mixed. Divide and shape mixture into 4 equal patties. Place on a cookie sheet and cover with aluminum foil. Refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes.. Cook patties on the preheated grill until cooked through, at least 7 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of the patties should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: Buffalo Chicken Stuffed Shells
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "cayenne pepper sauce (such as Frank's® RedHot®)"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) container', 'name': 'whipped ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'jumbo pasta shells'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar-Monterey Jack cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir ground chicken in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; drain and discard grease.. Melt butter in the skillet with the cooked chicken. Stir cayenne pepper sauce into the chicken mixture and remove from heat.. Squeeze as much moisture from the ricotta cheese using a cheese cloth or paper towels; put drained cheese in a large bowl. Add chicken mixture to the cheese and stir. Refrigerate until completely chilled, 3 to 4 hours.. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Prepare a 13x9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook pasta shells in the boiling water until cooked through but firm to the bite, about 10 minutes; drain. Rinse with cold water until no longer hot; drain.. Spoon chicken mixture into cooked pasta shells and arrange into the prepared baking dish. Sprinkle Cheddar-Monterey Jack cheese blend over the stuffed shells; season with salt and pepper.. Bake in preheated oven until the cheese is slightly melted and the stuffing is hot in the middle, 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Thai Chicken Larb
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken (preferably white meat)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red onion, halved and thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced scallions (mostly white parts)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh mint (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'minced fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemongrass paste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fish sauce, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt, or to taste'}
steps: Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken; cook and stir until chicken is broken into little pieces, about 5 minutes. Add red onion and scallions. Continue to cook until onion has softened and chicken has browned, about 2 minutes. Add lime juice, cilantro, mint, ginger, lemon grass, fish sauce, and red pepper flakes. Cook and stir until flavors blend, about 3 minutes more. Season to taste with sea salt.

name: Mozzarella-Stuffed Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-fat cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, grated'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh mozzarella, or as needed'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Combine ground chicken, egg, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic, olive oil, bread crumbs, basil, red pepper, garlic powder, salt, pepper, parsley, and oregano in a freezer-safe bowl and mix well. Place in the freezer for 15 minutes to make the mixture firmer and easier to handle.. Form into 14 equally sized meatballs using an ice cream scoop. Add a piece of mozzarella cheese to the center of each meatball, making sure cheese is covered by meat. Place meatballs on a nonstick baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until no longer pink in the centers and juices run clear, 20 to 25 minutes.

name: Chicken Lettuce Wraps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, cut into large dice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'rice wine vinegar, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grated fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce (such as Tabasco®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Asian (toasted) sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chunky peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'hot water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce (such as Tabasco®)'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large leaves of iceberg lettuce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, shredded'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped green onion, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Cook and stir ground chicken in a large skillet until the meat is crumbly and no longer pink, about 10 minutes. Drain excess grease. Stir red bell pepper into chicken; cook and stir until pepper is slightly softened, about 5 more minutes.. Whisk 1/2 cup soy sauce, rice wine vinegar, ginger, 5 dashes hot pepper sauce, and sesame oil in a bowl; pour over chicken mixture. Cook and stir chicken mixture with sauce over low heat until flavors have blended, 5 to 10 minutes.. Mash peanut butter with hot water in a small bowl until smooth; stir 3 tablespoons soy sauce and 5 dashes hot pepper sauce into the mixture. Set dipping sauce aside.. Form lettuce leaves into cup shapes and fill with chicken mixture. Top lettuce wraps with shredded carrots, sprinkle with green onion and cilantro, and a spoonful of peanut dipping sauce.

name: Air Fryer Chicken Kiev Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, crushed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'ground chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Mix butter, parsley, and garlic together in a bowl until well combined. Divide mixture into 12 equal parts on a baking sheet. Freeze until solid, about 20 minutes.. Shape ground chicken into 12 balls. Make a deep thumbprint in the center of each ball. Place a piece of frozen herbed butter in center, wrapping meat around it until fully covered. Repeat with remaining balls.. Beat eggs in a bowl. Combine panko, paprika, salt, and pepper in a separate bowl.. Dip 1 ground chicken ball in beaten eggs, then in seasoned bread crumbs. Dip ball back into egg and in seasoned bread crumbs once more. Repeat with remaining balls. Place on a baking sheet and freeze for 10 minutes.. Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Place half of the balls in the air fryer basket and spray with cooking spray.. Cook for 5 minutes. Flip balls over with tongs and spray again with cooking spray. Cook for 5 minutes more. Repeat with remaining chicken balls.

name: Creamy Chicken and Broccoli Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'rotini pasta, uncooked'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chipotle chile powder (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese, shredded'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion, finely diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream (Optional)'}
steps: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add rotini pasta and cook until al dente, 7 to 10 minutes. Drain, cover, and set aside until needed.. Melt butter in a saucepan over medium-high heat, and stir in 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add 1 cup broccoli; toss and cook just until tender, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle broccoli with flour, and cook 1 minute. Stir in the chicken broth, and bring to a boil. Pour in the milk, and stir to blend. Season with salt, pepper, and chipotle pepper powder, if desired. Reduce heat to medium, and simmer mixture until sauce thickens, 8 to 10 minutes. Mix in 1 cup Cheddar cheese and stir until melted. Remove from heat.. Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in another large skillet over medium-high heat. Stir in the onion, ground chicken, and remaining 1 cup of broccoli. Cook and stir until chicken is evenly browned and no longer pink, about 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Reduce heat, and cook until liquid is reduced, about 5 minutes.. Preheat oven broiler to High. Lightly grease 9x13 inch baking dish.. Toss the pasta with the broccoli sauce until evenly blended. Stir in the sour cream, if desired. Stir the broccoli sauce mixture into the chicken mixture. Spoon into the prepared baking dish. Top with remaining 1 cup Cheddar cheese.. Cook under preheated broiler until cheese melts and browns around the edges, 3 to 5 minutes.

name: Chicken Cordon Bleu Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '9', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cooked, diced ham'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Swiss cheese, cut into 1/2 inch cubes'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'canola oil for pan-frying'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Combine chicken, ham, and egg in a large bowl until well-blended. Gradually add bread crumbs until mixture loses its stickiness and can be easily formed into balls. Season with salt and pepper to taste.. Form chicken mixture around cheese cubes, forming 2-inch balls. Place on a plate.. Heat 1 1/2 inches of oil in a deep skillet to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Fry balls in hot oil until golden brown, about 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels and place in a baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until cooked through and cheese is soft, about 20 minutes. Cool briefly before serving.

name: Cheesy Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'roasted garlic light cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}
steps: Preheat an oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil, and spray with cooking spray.. Combine the chicken, eggs, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, red pepper flakes, Italian seasoning, garlic powder, vegetable oil, salt, and pepper in a large bowl; mix well. Form mixture into 20 meatballs; place on prepared pan.. Bake in center of preheated oven until juices run clear, 17 to 18 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: Chicken and Feta Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Kalamata-olive tapenade'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'crumbled feta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'crushed garlic'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'coarse-ground black pepper'}
steps: Mix chicken, oregano, tapenade, feta cheese, and garlic together in a bowl; form into 4 patties. Season burgers with salt and pepper.. Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate with olive oil.. Cook patties until charred on bottom, about 5 minutes. Flip the burgers and finish cooking, refraining from flattening with your spatula until no longer pink in the middle, about 5 minutes more. Drain on a plate lined with paper towels before serving.

name: Spicy Creole Chili
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Pure Wesson® Vegetable Oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'andouille sausage, cut into 1/2-inch slices'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped white onion'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'finely chopped garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': "Hunt's® Crushed Tomatoes"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, drained, rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'Ro*Tel® Hot Diced Tomatoes with Habaneros, undrained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Sour cream and chopped parsley'}
steps: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add ground chicken, sausage, and 1 teaspoon chili powder; cook 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Add cumin, paprika, salt, and remaining 1 teaspoon chili powder; cook 1 to 2 minutes more or until spices are fragrant.. name: Chicken Meatballs and Spaghetti
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(6 ounce) cans', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '2 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'whole-wheat spaghetti'}
steps: Stir together the crushed tomatoes, diced tomatoes, tomato paste, water, and basil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, and simmer for 15 minutes while preparing meatballs.. Mix together the ground chicken, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, eggs, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper in a medium bowl. Roll into 1 inch balls. Heat a large skillet over medium heat, and coat with cooking spray. Brown the meatballs on all sides. Add meatballs to the simmering pasta sauce and cook until internal temperature of meatballs reaches a minimum of 160 degrees F (72 degrees C), about 30 minutes..
