Cook until the pasta has cooked through, but is still firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain. Serve the meatballs and sauce over the cooked spaghetti.

name: Garlic Butter Zoodles with Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'salted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'zucchini noodles'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese, or to taste'}
steps: Mix ground chicken, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, egg, 2 garlic cloves, parsley, and red pepper flakes together in a large bowl. Season with kosher salt and black pepper and form into tablespoon-sized meatballs.. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook meatballs until golden brown on all sides and no longer pink in center, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a plate and wipe the skillet with a paper towel.. Melt butter in the same skillet; add remaining 3 garlic cloves and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add zucchini noodles to the skillet and toss into garlic butter; squeeze in lemon juice. Add meatballs and heat just until warmed through. Garnish with remaining Parmesan cheese to serve.

name: Ground Chicken Enchiladas
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'olive oil cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) envelope', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, cut into chunks'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10 ounce) cans', 'name': 'enchilada sauce'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Mexican-blend cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced black olives'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir ground chicken and onion in the hot skillet until chicken is no longer pink, crumbly, and onion is soft, 5 to 7 minutes. Sprinkle taco seasoning over top and add 1/2 cup water. Stir and cook until water is evaporated, 5 to 8 minutes. Add cream of chicken soup, cream cheese chunks, and sour cream. Stir until melted and fully incorporated. Stir in black pepper.. Pour one can of enchilada sauce into the prepared baking dish and spread to cover the bottom. Divide chicken mixture between the 8 tortillas and roll up tightly. Place filled tortillas in the prepared baking dish, seam-side down. Five should fit lengthwise and the remaining three should fit widthwise to fill the dish. Pour second can of enchilada sauce on top of rolled tortillas. Cover the dish tightly with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and remove foil. Sprinkle with both shredded cheeses, then green onions and black olives. Return to the oven and bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes more. Remove from the oven and allow to sit, 8 to 10 minutes before serving.

name: Buffalo Chicken Burgers with Blue Cheese Dressing
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light sour cream'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'reduced fat blue cheese crumbles'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'celery salt (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'poultry seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Kaiser rolls, split'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'leaves', 'name': 'iceberg lettuce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced celery'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat, and lightly oil the grate. Stir the sour cream, blue cheese, and Worcestershire sauce together in a small bowl; set aside.. Mix the ground chicken, 1/4 cup hot sauce, celery salt, poultry seasoning, paprika, and cayenne pepper together in a mixing bowl until evenly blended. Form into four 3/4-inch-thick patties.. Cook the chicken burgers on the preheated grill 6 to 7 minutes until well marked. Spray the uncooked top of the burger with cooking spray, and flip the burgers over. Brush the cooked side with 1 tablespoon hot sauce, and continue cooking until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 5 minutes more. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. To assemble the burgers, place a lettuce leaf on each roll bottom. Top with a burger patty, then spoon on 2 tablespoons of blue cheese sauce, and 2 tablespoons celery. Place the top of the roll on top to finish the sandwich.

name: Mexican Chicken Tortilla Lasagna
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'mild enchilada sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with green chiles (such as RO*TEL®), halfway drained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(1.25 ounce) package', 'name': 'reduced-sodium taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'crumbled queso fresco, divided'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'grated Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Spread about 4 tablespoons enchilada sauce over the bottom of an 8x6-inch baking dish. Pour remaining enchilada sauce into a medium bowl.. Heat oil in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook and stir until translucent, about 5 minutes. Add ground chicken and sauté until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Pour diced tomatoes and liquid into the skillet and stir in taco seasoning until incorporated.. To the enchilada sauce in the bowl, add 4 ounces queso fresco, 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon Mexican crema, and egg; stir to combine.. Trim tortillas to have a straight edge if desired. Lay two tortillas in enchilada sauce in the baking dish; top with some chicken mixture and some enchilada sauce mixture. Repeat layers (tortillas, chicken, sauce) twice more. Top with remaining queso fresco and Cheddar cheese.. Bake, covered, in the preheated oven for 35 minutes. Uncover and bake for 10 more minutes. Let rest for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

name: Greek Chicken Burgers with Feta
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh oregano'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'crumbled feta cheese'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Mix chicken, bread crumbs, egg, lemon juice, sun-dried tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper together in a bowl; form mixture into 5 patties. Divide feta cheese into 5 equal portions; place a portion of feta cheese atop each patty and fold chicken mixture around cheese to secure it in the center.. Cook patties on the preheated grill until no longer pink on the inside and juices run clear, 5 to 7 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read 165 degrees F (75 degrees C).

name: Buffalo Chicken Chili
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'carrot, peeled and finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, chopped'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground paprika'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "hot buffalo wing sauce (such as Frank's® REDHOT Buffalo Wing Sauce), or to taste"}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'white kidney or cannellini beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(19 ounce) can', 'name': 'red kidney beans, drained'}
steps: Heat olive oil and butter in a large pot over medium-high heat. Place chicken in the pot. Cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink, 7 to 10 minutes.. Stir in carrot, onion, celery, garlic, chili powder, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper. Cook and stir until onion is translucent and carrots begin to soften, 3 to 4 more minutes.. Stir in hot sauce, tomato sauce, crushed tomatoes, and white and red kidney beans. Bring to a boil, then simmer over medium-low heat until vegetables are tender and flavors have blended, about 1 hour.

name: Keto Chicken Cordon Bleu Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'blanched almond flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'ham steak, cubed into 20 even pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Swiss cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cracked black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced fresh parsley (Optional)'}
steps: Combine chicken, almond flour, salt, garlic powder, onion powder, and egg in a bowl. Form a small portion of chicken mixture into a 1 1/2-inch ball around a cube of ham; place on a plate. Repeat with remaining chicken mixture and ham, making 20 meatballs total.. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Brown meatballs for 3 minutes on one side; turn and cook an additional 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer meatballs onto a clean plate.. Return the skillet to medium heat and melt butter. Whisk in chicken broth and Dijon mustard; bring to a simmer for 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in heavy cream and whisk until sauce begins to simmer. Whisk in Swiss cheese until completely melted. Return meatballs to skillet and simmer until sauce has slightly thickened, 3 to 4 minutes. Season with cracked black pepper and parsley. Serve immediately. Sauce will further thicken upon cooling.

name: Thai Chicken Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground coriander seed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sweet chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'oil for frying'}
steps: In a large bowl, mix together chicken and bread crumbs. Season with green onion, ground coriander, cilantro, chili sauce, and lemon juice; mix well.. Using damp hands, form mixture into evenly shaped balls that are either small enough to eat with your fingers, or large enough to use as burgers.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Fry the chicken balls in batches until well browned all over.

name: Thai Ground Chicken Basil
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'peanut oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Thai chiles, sliced into thin rings'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'black soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh basil leaves'}
steps: Heat a wok over high heat until smoking. Pour in peanut oil, then immediately add garlic. Stir-fry garlic until it begins to turn golden brown, about 20 seconds. Mix in the ground chicken and continue cooking and stirring until the meat is crumbly and no longer pink, about 2 minutes.. Stir in the sliced chilies, soy sauce, and fish sauce. Cook for about 15 seconds to soften the chilies, then add the basil, and continue cooking until the basil has wilted.

name: Chicken Spaghetti Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, crushed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'kosher salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole peeled tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir chicken and onion together in hot oil until chicken has completely browned and onions tender, 7 to 10 minutes. Stir garlic, basil, kosher salt, and black pepper into chicken mixture; cook for 1 minute.. Blend tomatoes in a blender until smooth; pour over chicken mixture and bring to a simmer. Cook mixture at a simmer until hot and sauce has thickened slightly, about 10 minutes.. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over mixture; stir.

name: Spiced Chicken Loaf
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'herb stuffing mix, crushed into fine crumbs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'garlic pepper seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'barbeque sauce'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. In a large bowl, combine chicken, stuffing mix crumbs, cheese, egg, onion, salt, pepper, and garlic pepper seasoning. Mix together, then stir in ketchup and barbeque sauce. Mix well and pour mixture into a loaf pan.. Bake in the preheated oven for 50 minutes. Turn oven off and let sit in the hot oven for an additional 15 minutes.

name: Super Easy Polish Cabbage Rolls
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked white rice'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large head', 'name': 'cabbage'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'dried marjoram'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) cans', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.. Bring rice and water to a boil in a saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes. Allow rice to cool slightly.. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to a boil. Remove the core from the cabbage, and place cabbage in the boiling water. Remove the outer leaves as they soften. Set leaves aside.. Heat butter in a skillet over medium heat, and cook and stir onion until softened and translucent, about 5 minutes. Stir together cooked onion, ground chicken, cooked rice, eggs, garlic, salt, pepper, and marjoram in a bowl.. Place some of the meat mixture in the center of each cabbage leaf. Roll leaf and tuck ends in to enclose filling. Secure each roll with a toothpick if necessary. Place rolls into the prepared baking dish. Pour tomato sauce over the rolls.. Bake, covered, in the preheated oven until the meat in the rolls is no longer pink, 45 to 60 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of the casserole should read at least 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).

name: Baked Chicken Burgers with Mushrooms and Spinach
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'avocado oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced fresh mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chicken soup base (such as Better than Bouillon® Roasted Chicken Base)'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'name': 'sandwich buns'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x13-inch baking pan with 1/2 of the avocado oil.. Combine mushrooms, spinach, onion, and garlic in the bowl of a small food processor or blender and pulse several times until chopped into very small pieces, but not pureed.. Place ground chicken in a bowl. Add chopped vegetables, chicken base, salt, and pepper. Mix until vegetable pieces are evenly distributed. Divide mixture into 5 evenly sized portions and shape into patties.. Place patties onto the prepared baking sheet and lightly brush with remaining avocado oil.. Bake in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes. Turn on the broiler and broil each side until browned, 1 to 2 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Place each chicken burger on a bun.

name: Mexican Chicken Taco Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole kernel corn, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chiles (such as RO*TEL)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '7', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Mexican blend cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 9x13-inch casserole dish with nonstick spray.. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium to medium-high heat. Add ground chicken and onion; cook, stirring occasionally to break up the meat, until onion is mostly tender and meat is cooked through, about 5 minutes. Season with chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, and salt.. Add black beans, corn, diced tomatoes and green chiles, and tomato sauce; stir until well combined. Bring mixture to a low simmer and cook for about 10 minutes. Taste mixture and adjust the seasonings as desired.. Spoon a couple of good-sized scoops of meat mixture onto the bottom of the prepared casserole dish; spread into a thin layer. Place 3 or 4 tortillas over the sauce, breaking them in half as needed to make a fairly even layer without too much overlap. Spread the remaining meat mixture over the tortillas. Top with the remaining tortillas, again breaking into pieces as necessary to evenly cover the surface.. Cover with shredded cheese. Spray a piece of foil with nonstick spray; place over the casserole dish, sprayed-side down. (This helps prevent "cheese loss" when you remove the foil.). Bake in the preheated oven until casserole is bubbly and cheese is nicely melted, about 30 minutes. Allow to cool for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting into wedges or scooping out to serve.

name: Mexican Chicken Meatball Soup (Sopa de Albóndigas de Pollo)
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Roma tomatoes, quartered'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'quarts', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Roma tomatoes, seeded and finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'basmati rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'finely chopped mint leaves'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'zucchini, cubed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chayote squash - peeled, cored, and cubed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, peeled and cubed'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}
steps: Combine 4 tomatoes, 1/2 an onion, and garlic in a blender. Blend until smooth.. Heat oil in a soup pot over medium heat. Add blended tomato mixture; cook until mixture changes color, about 5 minutes. Add chicken stock, reduce heat, and simmer while you prepare meatballs.. Place ground chicken in a bowl. Add 3 chopped tomatoes, chopped onion, egg, rice, mint, oregano, salt, and pepper. Mix well with your hands until mixture is uniform. Take about 1/4 cup of mixture and form into round meatballs using wet hands. Place on a baking sheet. Repeat with remaining chicken mixture.. Bring stock mixture to a boil. Place a meatball into a ladle and submerge into boiling stock. Remove the ladle and repeat with remaining meatballs.. Place zucchini, chayote, and carrots into stock. Bring to a boil again. Lower heat, season with salt, and cover. Simmer until meatballs are no longer pink in the center and vegetables are soft, about 30 minutes.

name: Chicken Cheesesteak
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'American cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'hoagie rolls, split lengthwise'}
steps: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and bell pepper; cook and stir until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.. At the same time, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in another nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add ground chicken; cook and stir until chicken is crumbly and no longer pink, 8 to 10 minutes.. Add cooked onion and pepper mixture to the chicken; season with salt and pepper. Lay American cheese slices over top and cook until melted, 2 to 3 minutes.. Spread 1/4 of the cheesy chicken mixture evenly over each roll half and serve.

name: Ginger Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken (preferably dark meat)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plain dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large egg'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'peeled and minced fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced scallions'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'toasted sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'canola oil, or as needed'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Mix ground chicken, bread crumbs, egg, ginger, minced scallions, soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, and kosher salt together in a large bowl.. Form the mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls and arrange on the prepared baking sheet.. Brush the meatballs with canola oil. Bake in the preheated oven until browned and no longer pink in the center, about 13 minutes. Transfer to a platter.

name: Ground Chicken Stew
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'mild curry paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'zucchini, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'roma tomatoes, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}
steps: Mash garlic in the bottom of a saucepan. Stir curry paste into garlic; add onion and bell pepper. Cook and stir over medium-low heat until onion is golden, about 5 minutes.. Crumble ground chicken into the saucepan; add celery, carrots, zucchini, and tomatoes. Increase heat to medium, cover the saucepan with a lid, and cook until carrots have softened, 7 to 10 minutes.. Pour chicken broth and soy sauce over mixture; season with salt. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover with a lid, and simmer for 1 hour.

name: Spicy Chicken Burger with Beer Cheese Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light beer'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken breast halves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'hamburger buns'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half and half'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light beer'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground mustard'}
steps: Pour beer, paprika, chili powder, red pepper flakes, and garlic cloves into a resealable plastic bag. Add chicken, coat with the marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator, at least 4 hours.. Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Cook chicken on the prepared grill until no longer pink and juices run clear, 10 to 15 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Meanwhile, make cheese sauce. Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Whisk in flour; whisk continuously until mixture turns golden and forms a smooth paste. Pour in half and half and beer; stir until mixture thickens, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in cheese until melted, 2 to 3 minutes more. Stir in paprika, garlic powder, and ground mustard.. Toast hamburger buns on the grill until they show grill marks, about 2 minutes. Add your favorite toppings, pour cheese sauce on top, and serve immediately.

name: Chipotle Chicken Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'adobo sauce from chipotle peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'queso fresco'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'hamburger buns'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pico de gallo'}
steps: Stir mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon adobo sauce, lime juice, and the 1/8 teaspoon salt together in a small bowl; set aside. In a medium bowl, combine ground chicken, chipotle peppers, queso fresco, salt, and ground coriander. Form into 4 patties and place on squares of parchment paper. Refrigerate for 10 minutes to help patties firm up.. Preheat a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Brush skillet with butter and toast buns, cut side down, until lightly browned, about 1 to 2 minutes; set aside.. Heat oil in the same skillet over medium heat. Fry burgers until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 3 minutes per side. Turn heat off. Place cheese slices over patties and cover with a lid, letting the residual heat melt the cheese.. Spread chipotle mayo on bottom buns and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cilantro. Add chicken patty and top with pico de gallo.

name: Spicy Chicken Burgers With Mango Salsa
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'mango - peeled, seeded, and chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'hamburger buns'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'gouda cheese'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}
steps: Combine ground chicken, breadcrumbs, chopped onion, egg, lime zest, cilantro, garlic, and chipotle in a bowl. Shape mixture into four 1/4-pound patties.. Preheat an outdoor grill to medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Meanwhile, stir together chopped mangoes and the juice of the lime in a small bowl; set aside.. Grill chicken burgers on the preheated grill until chicken is no longer pink inside, juices run clear, and burgers show browned grill marks, 5 to 8 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. About 2 minutes before burgers are done, place hamburger buns onto the grill to toast, about 1 minute per side. About 1 minute before the burgers are done, top each burger with a slice of Gouda cheese, and let melt.. Spread each bun with 1 tablespoon mayonnaise and top with 1/4 cup shredded lettuce and grilled chicken burger. Spoon 1/4 of mango-lime mixture on each burger and top with the other half of the bun to serve.

name: Peanut Butter Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'creamy peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ginger'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Mix ground chicken, egg, bread crumbs, peanut butter, sweet Thai chili sauce, and ginger together in a large bowl.. Form the mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls and arrange on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until browned and no longer pink in the center, about 15 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: Easy Baked Ground Chicken Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry French onion soup mix'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'bacon, roughly chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'croissants, halved and toasted'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'Swiss cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, halved and cooked'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Combine ground chicken, bread crumbs, and soup mix in a large mixing bowl.. Place 4 ounces bacon in a food processor. Pulse 10 to 12 times and scrape down the sides. Combine the bacon with the ground chicken mixture; form into 6 patties and place on a baking sheet. Place in a freezer to chill for 12 minutes.. Bake patties in the preheated oven for 8 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and continue cooking until browned, no longer pink, and an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center reads at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 12 minutes more.. Meanwhile, set a sauté pan over medium heat. Add butter and once butter is melted, add onion and mushrooms. Allow to soften, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.. Assemble chicken burgers by adding a chicken patty to each croissant, top with Swiss cheese, bacon, and the onion mushroom mixture. Serve immediately.

name: 8 Chicken Meatloaf Recipes That Are Weeknight Winners
Baked Chicken Burger
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'blackened seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'liquid smoke flavoring'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'leaves', 'name': 'fresh basil, chopped'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Combine ground chicken, egg, oil, blackened seasoning, liquid smoke flavoring, garlic powder, and basil in a large bowl. Mix to combine, but be careful not to over handle the ground chicken.. Use a 1-cup measuring cup to form and portion 4 patties. Place into a cast iron skillet. Press patties with the back of the measuring cup to form burgers.. Bake in the preheated oven until cooked through and no longer pink in the centers, 18 to 20 minutes.

name: Chef John's Chicken Satay Burger
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Asian chile pepper sauce (such as sambal oelek), or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrots cut into thin matchsticks'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cucumber cut into thin matchsticks'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'jalapeño peppers cut into thin matchsticks'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'seasoned rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'coconut milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground turmeric'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'hamburger buns'}
steps: Combine peanut butter, lime juice, and 1 teaspoon Asian chile pepper sauce in a small bowl. Stir until thoroughly combined.. Mix carrot, cucumber, and jalapeño pepper in a bowl. Stir in vinegar and fish sauce. Set aside.. Mix garlic, coconut milk, cumin, turmeric, and remaining 1 teaspoon Asian chile pepper sauce in a bowl. Add bread crumbs, soy sauce, ground chicken, basil, salt, and cayenne pepper to taste and mix until thoroughly combined (mixture will be very soft).. Fry a small piece of chicken mixture in a nonstick skillet over medium heat until chicken is browned and no longer pink. Taste cooked chicken, then adjust raw chicken mixture to taste with more salt and cayenne if needed. Do not eat raw chicken mix.. Spoon 1/4 chicken mixture into skillet, forming a patty shape, and cook until bottom is browned, about 5 minutes. Flip patty and cook until browned, no longer pink inside, about 5 more minutes. Repeat with remaining chicken to make 3 more patties.. Spread about 1 teaspoon of peanut butter mixture onto each bun half. Top bun bottoms with a chicken patty, about 1/4 cup of carrot slaw, and 1 tablespoon cilantro leaves. Place bun tops on burgers to serve.

name: Ground Chicken Taco Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'dry taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'wheat hamburger buns, toasted'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'pepperjack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado - peeled, pitted and sliced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa, or to taste'}
steps: Preheat the outdoor grill to medium-high heat. Lightly oil the grill grate, and position it about 4 inches from the heat source.. Mix ground chicken, onion, garlic, taco seasoning, and egg together in a bowl until thoroughly blended. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Divide chicken mixture evenly and form into 4 soft patties.. Cook chicken patties on the preheated grill until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear, 5 to 8 minutes per side, depending on thickness. To serve, place each patty on one half of a hamburger bun, top with a slice of cheese, avocado slices, and desired amounts of jalapeño peppers and salsa. Cover with remaining half of bun.

name: Asian-Inspired Chicken Lettuce Wraps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'water chestnuts, drained and diced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'hoisin sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'light soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Sriracha'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced yellow onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'leaves', 'name': 'Bibb lettuce, or more as needed'}
steps: Set 2 to 3 tablespoons green onions aside for garnish. Combine remaining green onions, water chestnuts, hoisin sauce, soy sauce, Sriracha, rice vinegar, ginger, and red pepper flakes in a bowl.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add ground chicken, garlic, and sesame oil. Cook and stir until chicken is crumbly and no longer pink, 5 to 10 minutes.. Add hoisin mixture to the skillet and cook until heated through, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.. Fill lettuce leaves with chicken mixture and top with reserved green onions.

name: Chicken and Chorizo Chili
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'chorizo sausage, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'white beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can or bottle', 'name': 'beer'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'fire-roasted diced tomatoes, with juice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt to taste'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a Dutch oven or large pot over medium-high heat. Add chorizo; cook and stir until heated through, about 2 minutes. Transfer chorizo to a bowl using a slotted spoon. Add chicken; cook and stir until browned and crumbly, 5 to 6 minutes. Season with chili powder and cumin.. Stir chorizo, black beans, white beans, onion, bell pepper, and garlic into chicken; cook and stir until onion begins to soften, 5 to 6 minutes. Add beer; bring to a simmer. Add tomatoes, chicken stock, and tomato paste; simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes. Season with salt. Reduce heat to low and simmer until flavors blend, about 30 minutes.

name: Salsa Chicken Meatloaf
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'herb-seasoned croutons'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) jar', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and minced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground pork'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded pepperjack cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'barbecue sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x5-inch loaf pan.. Mix together croutons and salsa in a large bowl; set aside to soften, about 15 minutes.. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir onion, jalapeño pepper, and garlic in hot oil until onion is translucent, 5 to 8 minutes. Remove from heat.. Mix ground chicken, ground pork, pepper Jack cheese, cilantro, egg, taco seasoning, and Worcestershire sauce into crouton mixture; mash any unbroken croutons. Mix into onion mixture in the skillet, then transfer to the prepared loaf pan.. Mix together barbecue sauce and brown sugar in a small bowl, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Brush over meatloaf. Fold a 12-inch-long piece of aluminum foil into a tent and place over meatloaf.. Bake in the preheated oven until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 1 hour. Remove the foil tent for the last 10 minutes of baking. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of loaf should read at least 165 degrees F (75 degrees C). Remove meatloaf from the oven, cover with foil, and let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

name: French Onion Chicken Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'dry French onion soup mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onions, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red wine'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Gruyere cheese, shredded'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Mix ground chicken, bread crumbs, egg, onion soup mix, and garlic together in a medium bowl until the ingredients are well incorporated. Roll into sixteen 1 1/2-inch meatballs.. Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and sugar; saute until onions are softened, about 12 minutes.. Meanwhile, heat olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and cook, flipping occasionally, until edges are browned, about 4 minutes.. Transfer skillet to the preheated oven and bake until meatballs are no longer pink in the center, about 15 minutes. Check the meatballs halfway through and flip if they are browning too much on the bottom.. Add red wine, salt, and pepper to the onions and stir. Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes. Stir in beef broth and thyme. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and slowly stir in flour. Cook until slightly thickened, 2 to 3 minutes more.. Remove meatballs from the oven and pour onion sauce on top. Cover evenly with Gruyere cheese and return to the oven until melted, about 5 minutes.

name: Shami Kebab
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'yellow lentils'}, {'quantity': '4 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green chile peppers, finely chopped, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ginger-garlic paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garam masala'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'salt, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'cilantro, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed'}
steps: Place lentils in a container. Pour in enough water to cover and let soak, at least 30 minutes. Drain.. Combine drained lentils, 4 1/4 cups water, ground chicken, onion, green chile peppers, ginger-garlic paste, garam masala, and salt in a large pot. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer until water has been mostly absorbed and lentils are soft, 20 to 25 minutes.. Place the lentil mixture in a food processor and pulse until smooth. Stir in cilantro.. Shape mixture into patties and dip into beaten eggs.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Pan-fry patties in batches until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.

name: Air Fryer Oven Buffalo Chicken Jerky Sticks
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "cayenne pepper sauce (such as Frank's® RedHot®)"}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'celery seed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pink curing salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': "cayenne pepper sauce (such as Frank's® RedHot®)"}
steps: Combine ground chicken, 1/4 cup cayenne pepper sauce, sea salt, pepper, celery seed, garlic powder, onion powder, and pink curing salt in a large bowl; mix until evenly combined. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours, or overnight.. Use a jerky gun to form sticks of the meat mixture on air fryer oven racks.. Preheat the air fryer to 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).. Place racks into the air fryer and set timer for 2 hours. Flip the sticks over using a fork. Brush remaining 2 tablespoons cayenne pepper sauce over the tops. Air fry for 30 minutes more.. Let cool completely and transfer to an airtight container.

name: Lighter Mexican Meatloaf
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean ground turkey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole kernel corn, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'fire-roasted diced green chiles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mild chunky salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'dry taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plain dried breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg whites'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'enchilada sauce, divided'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Spray a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.. In a large bowl, mix together the ground turkey, ground chicken, black beans, corn, green chiles, salsa, taco seasoning, bread crumbs, and egg whites until thoroughly combined.. Form the mixture into a loaf shape and place into the prepared baking dish.. Pour half the enchilada sauce over the meatloaf.. Bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes.. Remove from oven and pour the remaining sauce over the loaf. Return to oven and cook until the meatloaf is no longer pink inside and the juices run clear, another 10 to 15 minutes. An instant-read meat thermometer inserted into the center of the meat loaf should read at least 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).. Slice and serve with pan sauce spooned over the slices.
